headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic began his final push for a possible third straight MVP by getting yet another triple-double.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has triple-double, Nuggets beat Cavaliers 115-109

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 31 points, including the final four in the last minute of overtime, and the Boston Celtics outlasted the Indiana Pacers 142-138 Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum has 31, breaks tie late in OT, Celtics outlast Pacers

headlines.description: — Wendell Carter Jr. tipped in Paolo Banchero's missed layup at the buzzer to give the Orlando Magic a 108-106 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wendell Carter beats buzzer with tip-in, Magic beat Pistons

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid slogged through illness and even played the rare role of victim on a dunk attempt. With a few big buckets and his own one-handed stuff of Ja Morant, Embiid ultimately...
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Embiid, Harris rally 76ers past Grizzlies 110-105

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 26 points, Jakob Poeltl had 21 points and a career-high 18 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the New Orleans Pelicans 115-110 on Thursday night for their sixth victory in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl has career-high 18 rebounds, Raptors beat Pelicans

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving have their first win together in Dallas — on the highest-scoring and best shooting night from 3-point range this season for the Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Irving get 1st tandem win as Mavs rout hapless Spurs

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen hit three free throws with 4.6 seconds left in overtime to give Utah the lead and finished with 43 points and 10 rebounds as the Jazz beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 120-119 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 43, rallies Jazz to OT win over Thunder

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James and Anthony Davis might finally have a supporting cast to help the Los Angeles Lakers make a push to get into the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Beasley scores 25 points, Lakers beat Warriors 124-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 31 points, Domantas Sabonis had his seventh triple-double of the season and the Sacramento Kings beat the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers 133-116 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Sabonis help Kings rout short-handed Blazers 133-116
